This is a placeholder info file using the Unreal Engine .uasset extension.
Note: Real .uasset files are binary assets created by Unreal Editor.

Language/Tech: Unreal Engine (C++ & Blueprints)
History:
- 1998+: Unreal Engine lineage; Blueprints for visual scripting
Advantages:
- High-end graphics, cross-platform, AAA tooling
Disadvantages:
- Heavy toolchain; steep learning curve
Alternatives:
- Unity, Godot, proprietary engines
Applications:
- Games, simulations, virtual production